                            <comment id="27231" author="costin" created="Thu, 1 Nov 2007 06:32:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve reverted the change since it seems that it doesn&apos;t work. Or actually it does but it forces people to use namespace prefix.&lt;br/&gt;
In short, a global attribute requires you to always use the following format:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;bean id=&quot;bla&quot; beans:class=&quot;..&quot; beans:scope=&quot;..&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The alternative would be to actually have an attributeGroup for each global attribute since then you don&apos;t have to use beans: prefix (the attribute doesn&apos;t have to be qualified).&lt;br/&gt;
However, the solution makes the XSD quite messy so it&apos;s up to you whether we go this way or not.&lt;br/&gt;
See article: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.xml.com/lpt/a/798&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.xml.com/lpt/a/798&lt;/a&gt; and the &quot;Why You Should Avoid Attribute Declarations&quot; chapter.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="43276" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Mon, 23 Mar 2009 11:42:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Costin, I&apos;ll leave this as-is for the time being unless redefinition of such attributes is too big a pain...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
